This trap trigger causes no damage of its own, but rather causes the nearest object sharing its tag to cast a spell defined by this trigger blueprint at the entering object.  This trigger is intended to be used with a Projectile Trap Origin placeable.

This type of trap trigger has a Search DC of 14 and a Disarm DC of 26.

Sets traps. Make sure you place the trap spawnpoints (Waypoints/Special 4) INTO the trigger area. You can place as many spawnpoints as you like. Small ones are good for doors, and large ones are nice in the middle of a room.


Variables:

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
spt_type = type of trap
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-1 = random
0 = Spike
1 = Holy
2 = Tangle
3 = Acid
4 = Fire
5 = Electricity
6 = Gas
7 = Frost
8 = Negative
9 = Sonic
10 = Acid Splash


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
spt_str = strength of the trap
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-1 = random
0 = minor
1 = average
2 = strong
3 = deadly
4 = epic (0nly Electric, Sonic, Fire and Frost are available!)

This is the default waypoint you may place to set a patrol path for a creature or NPC.
1. Create the creature and either use its current Tag or fill in a new one.
2. Place or make sure the WalkWayPoints() is within the body of the On Spawn script for the creature.
3. Place a series of waypoints along the route you wish the creature to walk.
4. Select all of the newly created waypoints and right click. Choose the Create Set option.
5. The waypoint set will have a set name of "WP_" + NPC Tag. Thus if an NPC with the Tag "Guard" will have a waypoint set called "WP_Guard". Note that Tags are case sensitive.

3. Place a series of waypoints along the route you wish the creature to walk.
4. Select all of the newly created waypoints and right click. Choose the Create Set option.
5. The waypoint set will have a set name of "WP_" + NPC Tag. Thus if an NPC with the Tag "Guard" will have a waypoint set called "WP_Guard". Note that Tags are case sensitive.
